h2. Spec::Rails - Installation - Quick Start

h4. Install

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_0_9_0/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_0_9_0/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

If you're using svn for your project, install with -x.

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_0_9_0/rspec
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_0_9_0/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h4. Bootstrap

Once the plugin is installed, you must bootstrap your Rails app with RSpec. Stand in the root of your Rails app and run:

<pre>
ruby script/generate rspec
</pre>

This will generate the various files needed to use RSpec with Rails and install RSpec Rake tasks.

h4. Run specs with rake ...

<pre>
rake spec
</pre>

h4. ... or run specs with scripts/spec

<pre>
ruby script/spec spec
</pre>

h2. Spec::Rails - Installation - Living on the Edge

If you prefer to live dangerously you can get the HEAD of the trunk.

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

If your own project is in Subversion and you'd like Spec::Rails to always follow HEAD, install with -x:

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec
ruby script/plugin install -x svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/trunk/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h2. Spec::Rails - Installation - The Long Version

Spec::Rails is a standard Rails plugin that can be installed with Rails' familiar <tt>script/plugin</tt> tool.
You also need rspec core in order to use it, and your installed rspec must be the same version as your installed
rspec_on_rails plugin. You can install rspec as a gem,
or you can install it as a plugin aside the rspec_on_rails plugin. We recommend the plugin approach, as it
allows you to maintain different versions of rspec_on_rails in different apps.

h3. Installation and use of the rspec gem

h4. Install the rspec gem

<pre>
gem install rspec
</pre>

h4. Run specs with rake ...

<pre>
rake spec
</pre>

h4. ... or run specs with the installed spec command.

<pre>
spec spec
</pre>

h3. Installation of rspec_on_rails and rspec as plugins

h4. Release 0.9 and later

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h4. Releases 0.7.5 to 0.8.x (not really recommended at this point)

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec_on_rails/vendor/plugins/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

h4. Releases < 0.7.5 (really not recommended at this point)

<pre>
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/rspec
ruby script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rspec/tags/REL_X_Y_Z/vendor/rspec_on_rails/vendor/plugins/rspec_on_rails
</pre>

